wwpQosMIB.description: The MIB module for the WWP QOS specific information.

VlanId.name: VlanId
VlanId.description: A 12-bit VLAN ID used in the VLAN Tag header.

wwpQosTable.name: wwpQosTable
wwpQosTable.description: A Table of QOS per vlan per port Entries.

wwpQosEntry.name: wwpQosEntry
wwpQosEntry.description: The QOS per vlan per port Entry in the Table.

wwpQosVlanId.name: wwpQosVlanId
wwpQosVlanId.description: Vlan ID for this instance of QOS. This Vlan Id should refer to the wwpVlanId in the WwpVlanEntry.

wwpQosPortId.name: wwpQosPortId
wwpQosPortId.description: Port ID for this instance of . Port ID's start at 1, and are consecutive for each additional port. This port Id should refer to the dot1dBasePort in the Dot1dBasePortEntry.

wwpQosRateLimit.name: wwpQosRateLimit
wwpQosRateLimit.description: The ingress traffic rate limit to be applied for this QOS entry.

wwpQosPriQueue.name: wwpQosPriQueue
wwpQosPriQueue.description: The TX-priority-queue value for this entry.

wwpQosRowStatus.name: wwpQosRowStatus
wwpQosRowStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'.

wwpQosStatsTable.name: wwpQosStatsTable
wwpQosStatsTable.description: A Table of QOS Stats per vlan per port Entries.

wwpQosStatsEntry.name: wwpQosStatsEntry
wwpQosStatsEntry.description: The QOS Stats per vlan per port Entry in the Table.

wwpQosStatsVlanId.name: wwpQosStatsVlanId
wwpQosStatsVlanId.description: Vlan ID for this instance of QOS. This Vlan Id should refer to the wwpVlanId in the WwpVlanEntry.

wwpQosStatsPortId.name: wwpQosStatsPortId
wwpQosStatsPortId.description: Port ID for this instance of . Port ID's start at 1, and are consecutive for each additional port. This port Id should refer to the dot1dBasePort in the Dot1dBasePortEntry.

wwpQosRxBytes.name: wwpQosRxBytes
wwpQosRxBytes.description: The number of bytes received for this QOS Entry.

wwpQosRxPkts.name: wwpQosRxPkts
wwpQosRxPkts.description: The number of pkts received for this QOS Entry.

wwpQosResetCounters.name: wwpQosResetCounters
wwpQosResetCounters.description: To reset the counters related to this QOS entry. A read on this object will always return the 'none'

wwpQosPriToQMapTable.name: wwpQosPriToQMapTable
wwpQosPriToQMapTable.description: A Table of mapping of an RX-priority to a TX-queue.

wwpQosPriToQMapEntry.name: wwpQosPriToQMapEntry
wwpQosPriToQMapEntry.description: The mapping Entry of an RX-priority to a TX-queue in the Table.

wwpQosRxPriority.name: wwpQosRxPriority
wwpQosRxPriority.description: The RX-prioroty value for this entry.

wwpQosTxPriQueue.name: wwpQosTxPriQueue
wwpQosTxPriQueue.description: The TX-priority-queue value for this entry.

wwpQosPortTable.name: wwpQosPortTable
wwpQosPortTable.description: A Table of QOS per port Entries.

wwpQosPortEntry.name: wwpQosPortEntry
wwpQosPortEntry.description: The QOS per port Entry in the Table.

wwpQosPortIndex.name: wwpQosPortIndex
wwpQosPortIndex.description: Port ID for this instance of . Port ID's start at 1, and are consecutive for each additional port. This port Id should refer to the dot1dBasePort in the Dot1dBasePortEntry.

wwpQosPortPriQueue.name: wwpQosPortPriQueue
wwpQosPortPriQueue.description: The TX-priority-queue value for this entry. The protocol entry in the hardware table will have the specified TX-priority-queue value. If no priority is associated with the port, then it is set to -1.

wwpQosPortQAlgo.name: wwpQosPortQAlgo
wwpQosPortQAlgo.description: The transmit queue servicing algorithm for the port. It can be either set to strict or credir(Weighted Fair Queuing).

wwpQosPortQApplyMode.name: wwpQosPortQApplyMode
wwpQosPortQApplyMode.description: This object decides whether to apply the config of all the queues together or one at a time. If this object is set to mgmtForAllQueues , then the Agent gets the config for all the 4 queues from the wwpQosPortQConfigTable and apply the configuration to Qos manager. This object shouldn't be set to mgmtForAllQueues unless all the 4 queues have been configured with Qdepth and QWeight. If it is set to mgmtPerQueue,then the agent just get the config for each configured queue at a time and apply the config to the Qos Manager.

wwpQosPortQConfTable.name: wwpQosPortQConfTable
wwpQosPortQConfTable.description: A Table of QOS per port per Queue Entries.

wwpQosPortQConfEntry.name: wwpQosPortQConfEntry
wwpQosPortQConfEntry.description: The QOS per port per queue Config Entry in the Table. This config will apply to the Qos Manager depending upon the wwpQosPortQApplyMode in the wwpQosPortEntry.

wwpQosConfPortId.name: wwpQosConfPortId
wwpQosConfPortId.description: Port ID for this instance of . Port ID's start at 1, and are consecutive for each additional port. This port Id should refer to the dot1dBasePort in the Dot1dBasePortEntry.

wwpQosPortQConfWeight.name: wwpQosPortQConfWeight
wwpQosPortQConfWeight.description: The bandwidth servicing percentage for the specified port transmit queue. This config will apply to the Qos Manager depending upon the wwpQosPortQApplyMode in the wwpQosPortEntry.

wwpQosPortQConfDepth.name: wwpQosPortQConfDepth
wwpQosPortQConfDepth.description: The maximum packet depth for the specified port transmit queue. The depth value corresponds to: Depth Value | Actual Number of Packets --------------|--------------------------- 0 | 32 1 | 64 2 | 128 3 | 256 The maximum total queue depth that can be configured for the port is a combination of depth values that would not exceed an actual packet count of 384. This config will apply to the Qos Manager depending upon the wwpQosPortQApplyMode in the wwpQosPortEntry.

wwpQosPortQConfStatus.name: wwpQosPortQConfStatus
wwpQosPortQConfStatus.description: The RowStatus to create the config entry. The RowStatus must be set to active for the wwpQosPortQApplyMode to be applied.

wwpQosPortQStatusTable.name: wwpQosPortQStatusTable
wwpQosPortQStatusTable.description: A Table of QOS per port per Queue Entries.

wwpQosPortQStatusEntry.name: wwpQosPortQStatusEntry
wwpQosPortQStatusEntry.description: The QOS per port per queue Entry in the Table.

wwpQosQPortId.name: wwpQosQPortId
wwpQosQPortId.description: Port ID for this instance of . Port ID's start at 1, and are consecutive for each additional port. This port Id should refer to the dot1dBasePort in the Dot1dBasePortEntry.

wwpQosPortQWeight.name: wwpQosPortQWeight
wwpQosPortQWeight.description: The current bandwidth servicing percentage for the specified port transmit queue.

wwpQosPortQDepth.name: wwpQosPortQDepth
wwpQosPortQDepth.description: The current maximum packet depth for the specified port transmit queue.

wwpQosTxAssignmentMode.name: wwpQosTxAssignmentMode
wwpQosTxAssignmentMode.description: The QoS TX-priority-queue assignment mode. This affect the behavior for ALL QoS entries. Setting the mode to useQos(0) will cause the ASIC to assign the TX-priority-queue value from the matching QoS entry to the frame. When set to useGreater(1), the ASIC will assign the greater of the two results: QoS Tx-priority or RX-Pri-To-Q TX-priority.

wwpQosPortTxAssignmentMode.name: wwpQosPortTxAssignmentMode
wwpQosPortTxAssignmentMode.description: The Port Protocol TX-priority-queue assignment mode. This affect the behavior for ALL Port Protocol entries. Setting the mode to usePort(0) will cause the ASIC to assign the TX-priority-queue value from the matching Port Protocol entry to the frame. When set to useGreater(1), the ASIC will assign the greater of the two results: Port Protocol Tx-priority or RX-Pri-To-Q TX-priority.
